This paper is about Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on preprocessing pipelines. The paper introduces a statistical method called uniblock to score and filter corpus with Unicode block information. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP and related topics. 

The paper also uses a Gaussian mixture model and variational inference, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. 

The paper involves text processing and filtering, which are related to information retrieval (IR) and search engines. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category. 

Finally, the paper uses statistical methods and models, which are also used in neural networks and deep learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category.
